title: Average life expectancy at birth in Sweden 2008 - 2018 , by gender
summary: The given chart is of multi-line type with 2 lines namely Men, and Women. The y axis represents Life expectancy in years and the x axis represents Year.
Overall Men, and Women are roughly constant,  throughout the Year
The ranking of the lines from topmost to botommmost is as follows: 1. Women, and lastly, 2. Men.
Throughout the period, Women generally had the highest Life expectancy in years relative to others with an average of 83.78, and it reached its maximum at 2014-2018 with a value of 84.1.
Men mostly had the least Life expectancy in years with a mean value of 80.06, which peaked at 2014-2018 with a value of 80.55.
